text: Much better than most people give it credit. It has a hundred emotions, all very intuitively labeled and is very easy and fast to navigate. It misses some key points that a certain competing app has (labels, like people, place and activity), and some basic functionality (like editing/removing existing entries, and offline plotting) is missing, so I won't be giving five stars for now. A bit too bad as I really like the execution so far â€“ I do hope that the devs listen and add these functionalities. Overall it is a very good app. Among the best mood trackers. Very well worth the price.

The idea, concept, and unique function of this app give it immense potential. Sadly, there are numerous programming glitches and/or device compatibility issues, along with grammatical/spelling errors within the app. These problems are holding it back from becoming the highly rated special purpose tool it could be.  The first major issue presents itself when attempting to register a date of birth. The app forces the data to be entered through the device calendar, making the process inefficient and frustrating.  After selecting an entry, certain dates will then display incorrectly, some even cause the app to crash without storing the DOB data.  A spelling error presents itself upon selecting the help option within the settings menu. The help page describes the purpose of the app, and, in the second bullet point, the word vocabulary is misspelled.  Although this is not a major issue in the app's functionality, it does not look very professional.  "Vocatulary" is not an official word in the English language, as far as I know.  There are also a couple of key options missing within the settings for the app.  Typically, an app giving a user the ability to create new tasks will then also include the ability to remove those same user-created tasks. The ability to delete old reminders that may no longer be needed and/or wanted in the reminders list would be nice for organizational purposes and to maintain optimal task processing.  As I initially stated, I really like the concept and purpose of this app, but these issues really need to be addressed in order to create a professional appearance, in turn, boosting ratings and increasing the appeal/popularity of this unique app.
Reports are no longer working and the strategies option fails to load

I'm a bit disappointed. I assumed this would be a great app for my class room... instead it is just a personal mood tracker. I would highly suggest for the ability to click a "dot" and it automatically be saved (multiple classroom accounts). This would make it easy for students to simply click the phone on the way into my door as my greeting and I would have instant data that I can show on my doc cam or to other students without the hassle of sticky notes or magnets. If you plan updating the app to allow this i'll keep it on my phone. Otherwise I would like a refund if possible.

The concept of this app is simple and powerful. I used it without fail on the iPhone for more than a year. This Android implement ration, however, is terrible and tremendously frustrating.   In less than a week of using the app, I've lost my data 3 times. This seems mostly related to the terrible authentication implementation, which is neither necessary nor valuable in anyway.   I have not once logged in successfully-I can't imagine that this was tested even once. By clicking Get Started I can enter the app and record moods, however, that fails randomly and unexpectedly.  This app is not worth your time as a free app, let alone a paid app.
